    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="section bg-black" id="faq">
        <div class="title-block">
            <p class="section-label">Common Questions</p>
            <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked <span class="accent">Questions</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-grid">
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Q: Do you charge a diagnostic fee just for looking at my car?</h4>
                <p>A: We charge a standard diagnostic fee of ¬£45 which covers up to one hour of investigation time using our professional diagnostic equipment. This fee is fully deducted from your final repair bill if you proceed with us. No hidden surprises.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Q: Can you work on my car if it's still under manufacturer warranty?</h4>
                <p>A: Yes. Under UK block exemption regulations, you are legally entitled to have your vehicle serviced at any qualified independent garage without voiding your manufacturer's warranty. We use OEM-equivalent parts and maintain a full service record.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Q: How long will my MOT take?</h4>
                <p>A: A standard MOT takes approximately 45‚Äì60 minutes. If any failures or advisories are identified, we will contact you immediately with a clear written quote before carrying out any remedial work.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Q: Do you offer a collection and delivery service?</h4>
                <p>A: Yes ‚Äî we offer free vehicle collection and delivery within a 5-mile radius of our garage for bookings over ¬£150. Please mention this when booking and we'll arrange a convenient time slot with you.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Q: What payment methods do you accept?</h4>
                <p>A: We accept all major debit and credit cards, bank transfers, and cash. Payment is due upon satisfactory completion of the work. For larger jobs, we may request a small deposit on parts before ordering.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Q: Are you able to source and fit manufacturer parts?</h4>
                <p>A: Absolutely. We can supply and fit genuine OEM parts, or high-quality aftermarket equivalents ‚Äî whichever you prefer and budget allows. We'll always advise which option is most appropriate for your vehicle and the nature of the repair.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
